  "text": "Debian is a popular Linux distribution used by over 32% of websites that run Linux. [CITATION_1] Software packages are installed and updated on Debian machines using the apt command-line program. The Debian software repository contains Release files for various versions of Debian, which are updated every time any package in the repository is updated. Each Release file contains a checksum for a Packages file, which contains a list of available software packages and their associated checksums for integrity checking.",
